The Trump family is the grift that keeps on grifting.



Case in point: Former first lady Melania Trump shilled gold necklaces on X Wednesday, joining her husband Donald in exploiting their Trump brand to sell products and make a quick buck. The baubles are sold by USA Memorabilia, which also sells Trump-themed collectibles, coins Christmas ornaments, NFT trading cards, and, curiously, Melania’s new memoir.&nbsp;



“Embrace boldness in your style this season with the ‘Vote Freedom’ necklace, which features the iconic Lady Liberty,” she wrote. “A tribute to America's enduring commitment to freedom, this piece is a statement of pride and empowerment.”



On Sept. 21, the Republican presidential nominee released a social media ad in a bid to sell $100 coins with his face emblazoned on them.&nbsp;



